section.section:
A request for proposals shall include a statement of:
The scope of the procurement contract;
The results to be achieved or services to be provided;
The factors, including price, that will be used in evaluating proposals; and
The relative importance of each factor.

If discussions are conducted, the board of trustees or its designee:
Shall conduct the discussions in accordance with regulations adopted by the board;
Shall provide an opportunity to participate to each responsible offeror who submits a proposal that, in the judgment of the board or its designee, is reasonably susceptible of being selected for award;
Shall treat all of the responsible offerors fairly and equally;
May allow all of the responsible offerors to revise their initial proposals by submitting best and final offers, if discussions indicate that it would be in the best interests of the college to do so;
May conduct more than one series of discussions and requests for best and final offers; and
May not disclose to an offeror any information derived from a proposal of or discussions with a competing offeror.
